Thatâ€™s why Docker is faster and lighter on Linux servers.

Important Interview Clarification
âŒ Wrong belief

â€œDocker containers are OS-agnosticâ€

âœ… Correct statement

Docker images are OS-specific (Linux vs Windows),
but Docker provides compatibility using a VM when needed.

Interview-Perfect Answer (Memorize)

â€œLinux containers require a Linux kernel. On Windows, Docker runs inside a lightweight Linux VM using WSL2 or Hyper-V. On AWS EC2, since the OS is already Linux, Docker runs containers directly without a VM.â€

